      <section eId="sec_396_V">
        <num>396-V</num>
        <heading>Operation of public automated blood pressure machines</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_396_V__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>These instruments serve merely as screening devices.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_396_V__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>They should not be used as a substitute for professional medical\nconsultation.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_396_V__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Blood pressure is subject to variation for many reasons. A single\nhigh or low reading cannot be interpreted as an indication of a health\nproblem.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_396_V__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Blood pressure readings can only be interpreted by a qualified\nmedical professional. Self diagnosis may be hazardous.\n  2. A violation of any of the provisions of subdivision one of this\nsection shall be punishable by a civil penalty of not more than two\nhundred fifty dollars.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
